Hi everyone, I’ve invited you to a meeting with LittleBits this morning at 11am
If you’d like, we could grab 5-10 minutes beforehand to discuss the context of the meeting. This is a follow-up to an in-person conversation we had with LB last week in NYC
<@U0GN0A9EV>
<@U0GN0A9EV|ivan> has joined the channel
<@U0265G76F|iamewald> has joined the channel

A little background on LittleBits: Last week we met with Joey Neal, a former colleague of Avery’s, who is now their VP of UX and Digital Products. He introduced us to one of his colleagues, Sean Schumer, who is working on a BLE product and is their only android developer.
We shared a bit of our knowledge on BLE, mentioned we’re doing some work in that space, (kept it all under wraps) and expressed in interest in helping out.
They followed up almost immediately wondering if we could help them out with their SDK.
Their mobile app is a bit of a test project at the moment, I believe we can (and should) try to help them out here, though the BLE project is the gateway to that.
Let’s meet at 10:50 in Courtyard to prep for the call.
And if you’re unfamiliar w/ littleBits: <https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qyxTjOS5a-U>
